#. Tag: title
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "Migration from &lxc; to <systemitem>libvirt-lxc</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:16
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since &sls; 12, &lxc; is integrated into &libvirt; library. This decision "
"has several advantages over using &lxc; as a separate solution&mdash;such as "
"a unified approach with other virtualization solutions or independence on "
"the kernel used. This chapter describes steps needed to migrate an existing "
"&lxc; environment for use with the &libvirt; library."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:25 lxc2libvirt.xml:34
#, no-c-format
msgid "Host Migration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The migration itself has two phases. You first need to migrate the host, "
"then the &lxc; containers. After that, you can run the original containers "
"as &vmguest;s in the &libvirt; environment."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:36
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrade the host to &sls; 12 using the official DVD media."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:41
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the upgrade, install the <systemitem>libvirt-daemon-lxc</systemitem> "
"and <systemitem>libvirt-daemon-config-network</systemitem> packages."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:48
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create a &libvirt; XML configuration <filename>lxc_container.xml</filename> "
"from the existing container <literal>lxc_container</literal>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:53
#, no-c-format
msgid "# virt-lxc-convert /etc/lxc/lxc_container/config &gt; lxc_container.xml"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:56
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check if the network configuration on the host is the same as in the "
"container configuration file, and fix it if needed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:62
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check the <filename>lxc_container.xml</filename> file for any weird or "
"missing configuration. Note that some &lxc; configuration options cannot be "
"mapped to &libvirt; configuration. Although the conversion should usually be "
"fine, check <xref linkend=\"lxc.diff\"/> for more details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:71
#, no-c-format
msgid "Define the container in &libvirt; based on the created XML definition:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:75
#, no-c-format
msgid "# virsh -c lxc:/// define lxc_container.xml"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:80 lxc2libvirt.xml:89
#, no-c-format
msgid "Container Migration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:82
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the host is migrated, the &lxc; container in &libvirt; will not boot. "
"It needs to be migrated to &sls; 12 as well to get everything working."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:91
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename>baseproduct</filename> file is missing (and <command>zypper</"
"command> keeps complaining about it). Create the relevant symbolic link:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:96
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"# ROOTFS=/var/lib/lxc/lxc_container/rootfs\n"
"# ln -s $ROOTFS/etc/products.d/SUSE_SLES.prod $ROOTFS/etc/products.d/"
"baseproduct"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:99
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Add the DVD repository. Note that you need to replace the DVD device with "
"the one attached to your container:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:103
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"# zypper --root $ROOTFS ar \\\n"
"cd:///?devices=/dev/dvd SLES12-12"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disable or remove previous repositories:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:109
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"# zypper --root $ROOTFS lr\n"
"  | Alias                       | Name                         | Enabled | "
"Refresh\n"
"--+-----------------------------+------------------------------+---------"
"+--------\n"
"1 | SLES12-12                   | SLES12-12                    | Yes     | "
"No\n"
"2 | SUSE-[...]-Server-11-SP3 38 | SUSE-[...]-Server-11-SP3 138 | Yes     | "
"No\n"
"\n"
"# zypper --root $ROOTFS rr 2"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:112
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrade the container:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:115
#, no-c-format
msgid "# zypper --root $ROOTFS dup"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:118
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Install the <emphasis>Minimal</emphasis> pattern to make sure everything "
"required is installed:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:122
#, no-c-format
msgid "# zypper --root $ROOTFS in -t pattern Minimal"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "Starting the Container"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:129
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the host and container migration is complete, the container can be "
"started:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:134
#, no-c-format
msgid "# virsh -c lxc:/// start lxc_container"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:136
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you need to get a console to view the logging messages produced by the "
"container, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: lxc2libvirt.xml:141
#, no-c-format
msgid "# virsh -c lxc:/// console lxc_container"
msgstr ""
